00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.099
 Through history 

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.051
 silver has been used as money 

00:00:02.051 --> 00:00:04.068
 for more time and in more places than gold. 

00:00:04.071 --> 00:00:05.094
 To function as money, 

00:00:05.094 --> 00:00:08.044
 A monetary item must have certain characteristics: 

00:00:08.050 --> 00:00:10.084
 1. It must be a means of exchange, 

00:00:10.097 --> 00:00:13.071
 It must have liquidity and be easily redeemable. 

00:00:13.074 --> 00:00:16.041
 It must be easily transportable (precious metals 

00:00:16.041 --> 00:00:18.044
 have a high value-to-weight ratio) 

00:00:18.044 --> 00:00:19.061
 And it must be durable. 

00:00:19.061 --> 00:00:20.079
 2. To be a unit of measure: 

00:00:20.081 --> 00:00:24.021
 it must be divisible into smaller units without destroying its value. 

00:00:24.021 --> 00:00:26.061
 Precious metals can be coined from ingots 

00:00:26.061 --> 00:00:29.086
 or melt into bars again, with low cost. 

00:00:29.086 --> 00:00:31.067
 It must be fungible, that is, 

00:00:31.067 --> 00:00:34.055
 one unit or piece is equivalent to another unit, 

00:00:34.055 --> 00:00:36.062
 reason why diamonds, works of art 

00:00:36.062 --> 00:00:38.037
 or real estate is not suitable as money. 

00:00:38.037 --> 00:00:41.041
 Must have a specific weight, or size or size 

00:00:41.041 --> 00:00:43.018
 Verifiably reliable. 

00:00:43.018 --> 00:00:45.078
 The third characteristic is that it must be a store of value. 

00:00:45.078 --> 00:00:48.015
 It must be durable in the long term and not perishable 

00:00:48.015 --> 00:00:50.063
 or subject to deterioration. 

00:00:50.067 --> 00:00:52.044
 It must have a stable value. 

00:00:52.044 --> 00:00:54.073
 It must be hard to fake and the genuine 

00:00:54.073 --> 00:00:56.038
 easily recognizable 

00:00:56.038 --> 00:00:58.042
 Currently silver is not used as money 

00:00:58.042 --> 00:00:59.084
 because it does not circulate. 

00:00:59.084 --> 00:01:02.084
 But it does provide a crucial role as a store of value. 

00:01:02.084 --> 00:01:04.084
 Why do gold and silver have value? 

